1
00:00:07,674 --> 00:00:09,926
It smells of nature.

2
00:00:11,928 --> 00:00:14,597
- Are you driving today?
- I am.

3
00:00:15,473 --> 00:00:16,724
I'm a bit nervous.

4
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:17,684
Are you really?

5
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:19,185
Gosh.

6
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:21,437
Now that I'm in the car,

7
00:00:21,438 --> 00:00:23,063
- it feels like we're getting started.
- Right?

8
00:00:23,064 --> 00:00:24,356
- I'm nervous.
- Me too.

9
00:00:24,357 --> 00:00:26,191
- Wait, I'm not sure how to do this.
- What?

10
00:00:26,192 --> 00:00:28,236
HOW DO YOU START THE ENGINE?

11
00:00:28,820 --> 00:00:29,904
Here it is.

12
00:00:32,407 --> 00:00:33,657
The weather is nice.

13
00:00:33,658 --> 00:00:37,202
It's cooled down after the rain.

14
00:00:37,203 --> 00:00:38,370
IT'S NICE INSIDE THE CAR TOO

15
00:00:38,371 --> 00:00:40,164
I'm excited.

16
00:00:40,165 --> 00:00:42,500
EXCITED SCREAMING

17
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:46,296
Hello.

18
00:00:47,881 --> 00:00:49,506
How have you been, Yong-jin?

19
00:00:49,507 --> 00:00:51,050
Life is good.

20
00:00:51,051 --> 00:00:53,260
They're so cute. Look at them.

21
00:00:53,261 --> 00:00:54,512
Let's pretend to be students.

22
00:01:00,143 --> 00:01:01,351
That was bad.

23
00:01:01,352 --> 00:01:02,311
Sorry.

24
00:01:02,312 --> 00:01:03,937
That was terrible.

25
00:01:03,938 --> 00:01:05,105
THE YOUNGEST ARE READY FOR CLASS

26
00:01:05,106 --> 00:01:07,066
- Hey, kiddos.
- Hello.

27
00:01:07,067 --> 00:01:08,525
You're so cute.

28
00:01:08,526 --> 00:01:09,443
Hello.

29
00:01:09,444 --> 00:01:11,071
Let's go and protect the Earth!

30
00:01:11,696 --> 00:01:13,906
We got here using the address.

31
00:01:13,907 --> 00:01:14,907
- Yes.
- That's right.

32
00:01:14,908 --> 00:01:16,200
Are there no clues here this time?

33
00:01:16,201 --> 00:01:17,451
- Open that.
- There's nothing.

34
00:01:17,452 --> 00:01:19,328
- Really?
- I opened it as soon as I got in.

35
00:01:19,329 --> 00:01:20,454
There's nothing.

36
00:01:20,455 --> 00:01:22,081
- Found it!
- It's here.

37
00:01:22,082 --> 00:01:24,792
THE MISSION WAS IN THE GLOVE BOX LAST TIME

38
00:01:24,793 --> 00:01:25,918
- Anything back here?
- Anything?

39
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:26,877
- Here?
- Is there anything?

40
00:01:26,878 --> 00:01:28,420
- I don't see anything.
- There's nothing.

41
00:01:28,421 --> 00:01:30,714
There's nothing back here.

42
00:01:30,715 --> 00:01:32,007
What's in the bag?

43
00:01:32,008 --> 00:01:33,926
I have snacks.

44
00:01:33,927 --> 00:01:35,636
WE NEED TO KEEP OUR STRENGTH UP

45
00:01:35,637 --> 00:01:38,639
I think the navigation
already knows our destination.

46
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:40,390
- That's the address, right?
- Yes.

47
00:01:40,391 --> 00:01:41,767
- Should we set off?
- Should we?

48
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:43,769
- Let's go.
- Okay.

49
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:45,145
Are you okay to drive?

50
00:01:45,146 --> 00:01:47,231
I'll try my best.

51
00:01:47,232 --> 00:01:49,484
It feels like we're in San Francisco
since Gabee's driving.

52
00:01:53,905 --> 00:01:56,990
You can tell she picked up English
by watching <i>Gossip Girl.</i>

53
00:01:56,991 --> 00:01:59,076
- It's the only English I know.
- I see.

54
00:01:59,077 --> 00:02:00,494
I can't speak formal English.

55
00:02:00,495 --> 00:02:02,079
It's because you learned from <i>Gossip Girl.</i>

56
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,456
You can only speak like a Valley girl.

57
00:02:11,798 --> 00:02:13,049
Yong-jin, how do I release…

58
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:16,343
- How do I…
- Start the car?

59
00:02:16,344 --> 00:02:17,719
- What do you mean?
- This thing…

60
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:19,972
- I mean the parking brake.
- What?

61
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:21,431
- Press the pedal.
- There's nothing to it.

62
00:02:21,432 --> 00:02:23,475
- Press the pedal, then turn it.
- Isn't it this lever?

63
00:02:23,476 --> 00:02:25,269
- I don't mean that.
- Okay.

64
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:26,562
Oh, you're right.

65
00:02:26,563 --> 00:02:28,272
IN SHOCK

66
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:29,606
We've started already.

67
00:02:29,607 --> 00:02:31,608
- This was the mission.
- Hear me out.

68
00:02:31,609 --> 00:02:32,818
It's my first time in this car.

69
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:34,069
It can be confusing.

70
00:02:34,070 --> 00:02:35,487
I need a minute.

71
00:02:35,488 --> 00:02:37,323
I'm sweating.

72
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:39,867
I was just a bit nervous.

73
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:43,579
I want to state for the record
that I'm a good driver.

74
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:44,997
- Should we get going?
- Let's go.

75
00:02:44,998 --> 00:02:45,914
Are you strapped in?

76
00:02:45,915 --> 00:02:47,958
Let's go where the navigation leads us.

77
00:02:47,959 --> 00:02:49,209
Okay.

78
00:02:49,210 --> 00:02:50,795
Drive slowly, Gabee.

79
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:53,672
Gabee, the D stands for "drive."

80
00:02:53,673 --> 00:02:56,508
EMBARRASSED

81
00:02:56,509 --> 00:02:59,052
I'll drive really slowly.

82
00:02:59,053 --> 00:02:59,970
Okay.

83
00:02:59,971 --> 00:03:01,388
- Please go really slowly.
- Okay.

84
00:03:01,389 --> 00:03:02,514
I trust you, Gabee.

85
00:03:02,515 --> 00:03:04,600
I'm feeling good.

86
00:03:04,601 --> 00:03:06,143
Oh, I'm going the wrong way.

87
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:07,352
TERRIFIED

88
00:03:07,353 --> 00:03:08,353
From the beginning?

89
00:03:08,354 --> 00:03:09,689
RESIGNED

90
00:03:10,273 --> 00:03:11,190
It's going great.

91
00:03:11,191 --> 00:03:12,983
It's thrilling.

92
00:03:12,984 --> 00:03:14,443
Don't be nervous.

93
00:03:14,444 --> 00:03:15,862
Just relax, everyone.

94
00:03:18,156 --> 00:03:20,866
What could today's mission be?

95
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:23,660
- I have no idea.
- Right? I wonder what it is.

96
00:03:23,661 --> 00:03:25,037
What's that sound?

97
00:03:25,038 --> 00:03:26,121
- John?
- Is it the detector?

98
00:03:26,122 --> 00:03:27,540
Something's beeping, right?

99
00:03:32,962 --> 00:03:34,087
Wait!

100
00:03:34,088 --> 00:03:35,505
It's not this.

101
00:03:35,506 --> 00:03:36,590
It's not the detector.

102
00:03:36,591 --> 00:03:38,009
THE X-WAVE DETECTOR IS SILENT

103
00:03:39,510 --> 00:03:41,261
- Oh, it's your timer.
- Is it my camera?

104
00:03:41,262 --> 00:03:42,846
What's wrong with you?

105
00:03:42,847 --> 00:03:44,306
- That scared me!
- Calm down, friends.

106
00:03:44,307 --> 00:03:46,016
- Do-hoon!
- What on earth?

107
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:49,103
- I have no idea.
- Right? I wonder what it is.

108
00:03:49,604 --> 00:03:50,604
What's that sound?

109
00:03:50,605 --> 00:03:51,605
- John?
- Is it the detector?

110
00:03:51,606 --> 00:03:52,981
Something's beeping, right?

111
00:03:52,982 --> 00:03:53,941
Wait!

112
00:03:53,942 --> 00:03:55,859
- It's not this.
- It's not the detector.

113
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:57,569
- Oh, it's your timer.
- Is it my camera?

114
00:03:57,570 --> 00:03:59,112
What's wrong with you?

115
00:03:59,113 --> 00:04:02,074
I thought it was the X-Wave Detector.

116
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:03,742
EMBARRASSED

117
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:07,538
We're all so bad with technology.

118
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:09,873
- I'm sorry, but it's true.
- I've sorted it.

119
00:04:09,874 --> 00:04:12,376
- It's quite far.
- Right?

120
00:04:12,377 --> 00:04:13,710
It's quite a long drive.

121
00:04:13,711 --> 00:04:16,129
What have we not done yet?

122
00:04:16,130 --> 00:04:18,757
We've dealt with the mutants.

123
00:04:18,758 --> 00:04:20,801
What else is there to do?

124
00:04:20,802 --> 00:04:22,261
We've done room missions.

125
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:25,555
Isn't it time for us to go up against NIX?

126
00:04:25,556 --> 00:04:27,182
- It's a school.
- School?

127
00:04:27,183 --> 00:04:29,227
- Please no…
- Come on.

128
00:04:29,936 --> 00:04:32,521
- A school is the worst.
- I hate it.

129
00:04:32,522 --> 00:04:34,731
- No way!
- I really hope it's not that.

130
00:04:34,732 --> 00:04:36,359
We are dressed like students.

131
00:04:37,151 --> 00:04:38,694
Is this a school uniform?

132
00:04:38,695 --> 00:04:40,153
- I thought we were detectives.
- Me too.

133
00:04:40,154 --> 00:04:41,321
Isn't it a <i>Kingsman</i> concept?

134
00:04:41,322 --> 00:04:43,282
Doesn't it feel like <i>All of Us Are Dead?</i>

135
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:44,449
I hate that so much.

136
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:45,909
- I'm scared.
- The student zombies.

137
00:04:45,910 --> 00:04:47,077
There has to be a reason

138
00:04:47,078 --> 00:04:49,413
- we're starting at night.
- You're right.

139
00:04:49,414 --> 00:04:52,582
- There has to be a reason.
- Today's mission is…

140
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:54,334
It's 7:30 p.m. right now.

141
00:04:54,335 --> 00:04:56,003
There's a reason we're starting so late.

142
00:04:56,004 --> 00:04:58,046
How much will they scare us this time?

143
00:04:58,047 --> 00:05:00,424
Gabee's driving is the scariest thing yet.

144
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:01,633
GIGGLE

145
00:05:01,634 --> 00:05:03,260
It seems like…

146
00:05:03,261 --> 00:05:04,804
- We're nearly there.
- What is it?

147
00:05:05,513 --> 00:05:07,723
- Is the road wide enough?
- Wait, what?

148
00:05:07,724 --> 00:05:08,724
We're heading this way?

149
00:05:08,725 --> 00:05:10,310
- What on earth?
- The road is so…

150
00:05:11,144 --> 00:05:14,354
A HIGH AND NARROW ROAD

151
00:05:14,355 --> 00:05:15,731
We're going up?

152
00:05:15,732 --> 00:05:16,815
- This is…
- What on earth?

153
00:05:16,816 --> 00:05:17,900
Wait a minute.

154
00:05:19,068 --> 00:05:20,736
We're heading into a mountain.

155
00:05:20,737 --> 00:05:23,364
- It's just a mountain.
- I'm so scared.

156
00:05:24,032 --> 00:05:25,782
- I'll go slowly.
- I feel stressed.

157
00:05:25,783 --> 00:05:27,659
I'm dreading this.

158
00:05:27,660 --> 00:05:29,494
What could possibly be here?

159
00:05:29,495 --> 00:05:30,620
HEADING INTO A SECLUDED AREA

160
00:05:30,621 --> 00:05:32,122
- It's a rice field.
- There's nothing here.

161
00:05:32,123 --> 00:05:33,541
Is it an outdoor mission?

162
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:35,459
This must be the place.

163
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:37,627
I'm so scared.

164
00:05:37,628 --> 00:05:38,587
Why here?

165
00:05:38,588 --> 00:05:39,922
- What's that?
- There's something here.

166
00:05:40,506 --> 00:05:42,466
- What is that?
- Why is that here?

167
00:05:42,467 --> 00:05:43,759
- Oh, my.
- What is that?

168
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:45,635
Why is there a village bus stop here?

169
00:05:45,636 --> 00:05:48,597
- A bus must pass through here!
- It's a bus stop.

170
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:52,225
- I see a milk carton and papers.
- There's something.

171
00:05:52,226 --> 00:05:56,438
<i>We ended up in the middle of a mountain</i>

172
00:05:56,439 --> 00:05:58,648
<i>surrounded by rice paddies.</i>

173
00:05:58,649 --> 00:06:01,611
<i>Then, totally out of the blue,</i>

174
00:06:02,362 --> 00:06:04,197
<i>there was a bus stop.</i>

175
00:06:04,739 --> 00:06:06,740
There was also milk on a newspaper.

176
00:06:06,741 --> 00:06:08,950
It was plain milk, which is my favorite.

177
00:06:08,951 --> 00:06:10,077
QUICK SCAN

178
00:06:10,078 --> 00:06:12,079
It says the bus arrival information
is unavailable.

179
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:14,331
It wasn't an old abandoned bus stop.

180
00:06:14,332 --> 00:06:15,999
The bus arrival display was still working.

181
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:20,128
It was a high-tech bus stop,
which was very strange.

182
00:06:20,129 --> 00:06:22,547
Why would a bus pass through here?

183
00:06:22,548 --> 00:06:23,424
I'll park here.

184
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:25,509
If you look outside…

185
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:27,761
It's not raining,
but she's got the wipers on!

186
00:06:27,762 --> 00:06:29,096
Her driving scares me the most!

187
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:31,390
EMBARRASSED

188
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:32,974
Should we head over to the bus stop?

189
00:06:32,975 --> 00:06:33,892
- Yes.
- Let's get out.

190
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:36,436
- We might find details of the mission.
- I'm scared.

191
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:38,855
- Let's check it out first.
- Okay.

192
00:06:38,856 --> 00:06:41,233
It's the kind of thing we hate, Do-hoon.

193
00:06:41,234 --> 00:06:42,692
I really hate this.

194
00:06:42,693 --> 00:06:44,277
I mean…

195
00:06:44,278 --> 00:06:45,862
What's with the milk?

196
00:06:45,863 --> 00:06:47,240
- It must be stale by now.
- Right?

197
00:06:47,949 --> 00:06:49,866
This is so suspicious.

198
00:06:49,867 --> 00:06:50,701
What's going on?

199
00:06:51,369 --> 00:06:53,870
- How can a bus get up here?
- Do we get on a bus?

200
00:06:53,871 --> 00:06:56,748
STARTING OFF CAUTIOUS

201
00:06:56,749 --> 00:06:59,127
It's clearly meant to get our attention.

202
00:06:59,752 --> 00:07:01,211
I have a bad feeling.

203
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:03,880
Is the clue in the text like last time?

204
00:07:03,881 --> 00:07:04,881
There must be a code.

205
00:07:04,882 --> 00:07:05,841
SCANNING THE SUSPICIOUS PAPER

206
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:07,551
"Jangil-myeon News."

207
00:07:07,552 --> 00:07:09,344
"Following the mountains and waters."

208
00:07:09,345 --> 00:07:11,012
It's today's date.

209
00:07:11,013 --> 00:07:12,890
- It's July 8th.
- Yes.

210
00:07:13,724 --> 00:07:14,891
It has our zodiac signs.

211
00:07:14,892 --> 00:07:15,976
TODAY'S ZODIAC HOROSCOPE

212
00:07:15,977 --> 00:07:17,853
- Should we check ours?
- Yes.

213
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:19,312
- My zodiac sign is the Rooster.
- Rooster?

214
00:07:19,313 --> 00:07:22,315
- "If you feel afraid, laugh loudly."
- "If you feel afraid, laugh loudly."

215
00:07:22,316 --> 00:07:24,568
LAUGHING LOUDLY

216
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:26,903
That's a good laugh. You're good at this.

217
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:27,946
It's the Dog zodiac sign.

218
00:07:27,947 --> 00:07:30,490
"Water energy is in full force today."

219
00:07:30,491 --> 00:07:32,033
"Stay close to water."

220
00:07:32,034 --> 00:07:33,493
- Water?
- Yes.

221
00:07:33,494 --> 00:07:34,828
- This is new.
- What's yours, Karina?

222
00:07:34,829 --> 00:07:35,912
Mine is a Dragon.

223
00:07:35,913 --> 00:07:37,080
"Read many texts."

224
00:07:37,081 --> 00:07:38,791
"It will help solve problems."

225
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:40,417
What's yours, John?

226
00:07:40,418 --> 00:07:41,543
It's a Dragon.

227
00:07:41,544 --> 00:07:43,671
- You're a Dragon too?
- Yes.

228
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:45,465
You're a Dragon?

229
00:07:45,965 --> 00:07:47,549
- I'm 12 years older.
- You're a Dragon?

230
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:49,176
FEELING AWKWARD

231
00:07:49,177 --> 00:07:50,427
You need to read a lot, John.

232
00:07:50,428 --> 00:07:51,803
- It will help solve problems.
- I'm old.

233
00:07:51,804 --> 00:07:53,388
- What's yours, Do-hoon?
- I'm a Tiger.

234
00:07:53,389 --> 00:07:55,015
"You must stick to the plan."

235
00:07:55,016 --> 00:07:57,559
"If things don't go to plan,
push the person next to you."

236
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:59,227
- Goodness!
- What does it mean?

237
00:07:59,228 --> 00:08:01,313
- If things don't go well…
- You push them.

238
00:08:01,314 --> 00:08:02,981
- What's yours, Yong-jin?
- Mine is an Ox.

239
00:08:02,982 --> 00:08:04,316
It's this one.

240
00:08:04,317 --> 00:08:05,151
It says…

241
00:08:06,486 --> 00:08:07,652
It says today is your lucky day.

242
00:08:07,653 --> 00:08:08,778
- Really?
- Yes.

243
00:08:08,779 --> 00:08:10,405
"Take the lead with confidence."

244
00:08:10,406 --> 00:08:11,364
- "But."
- "But."

245
00:08:11,365 --> 00:08:13,408
"Take care in a setting
where someone has a blade or spear."

246
00:08:13,409 --> 00:08:15,785
Karina?

247
00:08:15,786 --> 00:08:17,913
- Don't look at me!
- It said blade or spear?

248
00:08:17,914 --> 00:08:19,372
- It's not me!
- Why is there a blade?

249
00:08:19,373 --> 00:08:21,124
- Someone with a blade or spear.
- Leave me alone.

250
00:08:21,125 --> 00:08:22,459
Could it be--

251
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:24,128
- What?
- Oh, gosh.

252
00:08:26,714 --> 00:08:28,673
<i>Here is your XIN mission information.</i>

253
00:08:28,674 --> 00:08:29,592
It's about the mission.

254
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:31,718
HERE IS YOUR XIN MISSION

255
00:08:31,719 --> 00:08:32,678
That's so cool.

256
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:35,472
<i>Last time, it was an ATM.</i>

257
00:08:35,473 --> 00:08:39,684
<i>This time, the mission appeared
on a bus arrival display.</i>

258
00:08:39,685 --> 00:08:41,978
<i>The incident took place</i>

259
00:08:41,979 --> 00:08:44,690
