638
00:22:50,452 --> 00:22:51,827
- He fell off the radar?
- Yes.

639
00:22:51,828 --> 00:22:53,704
Who is "him"?

640
00:22:53,705 --> 00:22:54,789
CAN YOU STILL NOT REACH HIM?

641
00:22:54,790 --> 00:22:55,956
- It doesn't say.
- They don't say.

642
00:22:55,957 --> 00:22:57,834
- At the start…
- They mentioned King MS.

643
00:22:58,502 --> 00:23:00,337
- King MS?
- King MS?

644
00:23:01,213 --> 00:23:02,129
Is that him?

645
00:23:02,130 --> 00:23:03,422
- I think so.
- I think it's a nickname.

646
00:23:03,423 --> 00:23:05,716
We've got another chat left, right?

647
00:23:05,717 --> 00:23:07,469
It's titled "Mysterious Tarot."

648
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:10,638
"Advert: Exclusive Scoop.
Chilling Prenatal Dream of Lee Yong-jin!"

649
00:23:10,639 --> 00:23:12,098
"A prenatal dream is just a dream."

650
00:23:12,099 --> 00:23:13,974
"Stop believing
in baseless superstitions."

651
00:23:13,975 --> 00:23:14,892
"Tarot is different."

652
00:23:14,893 --> 00:23:16,977
"It combines astrology,
symbolism, and statistical trends."

653
00:23:16,978 --> 00:23:17,978
Hold up.

654
00:23:17,979 --> 00:23:19,021
- You read tarot.
- It's you.

655
00:23:19,022 --> 00:23:22,066
- No, it's not. Why turn on me?
- It might be a different Yong-jin.

656
00:23:22,067 --> 00:23:24,860
I'm barely coping as it is.
Don't be like this.

657
00:23:24,861 --> 00:23:25,861
I mean it.

658
00:23:25,862 --> 00:23:27,238
I'm struggling right now.

659
00:23:27,239 --> 00:23:28,280
Don't do this to me.

660
00:23:28,281 --> 00:23:29,865
- I'm warning you.
- All right.

661
00:23:29,866 --> 00:23:31,200
- Look here.
- I mean it.

662
00:23:31,201 --> 00:23:33,661
- Okay.
- Doesn't that say King MS?

663
00:23:33,662 --> 00:23:34,538
It does.

664
00:23:36,331 --> 00:23:37,665
"WHY AREN'T YOU REPLYING?"

665
00:23:37,666 --> 00:23:39,042
PRIVATE CHAT WITH KING MS

666
00:23:40,043 --> 00:23:41,460
- You're right.
- It's him.

667
00:23:41,461 --> 00:23:43,337
"It's me, Oh Deok-u. I emailed you."

668
00:23:43,338 --> 00:23:44,548
"Is this the right chat?"

669
00:23:45,173 --> 00:23:46,882
"I'm a real fan."

670
00:23:46,883 --> 00:23:48,008
"I'll go on the 29th."

671
00:23:48,009 --> 00:23:49,511
- "I'm trusting you."
- Oh, here…

672
00:23:50,095 --> 00:23:51,846
"Do you know Baeksudam Garden?"

673
00:23:51,847 --> 00:23:53,807
"It's a super famous
abandoned house in this area."

674
00:23:54,349 --> 00:23:55,558
"There are many creepy rumors."

675
00:23:55,559 --> 00:23:57,935
"It was a restaurant
that went bust three years ago."

676
00:23:57,936 --> 00:23:59,603
"All the customers died,

677
00:23:59,604 --> 00:24:02,314
and the owner got possessed by a ghost
and committed suicide."

678
00:24:02,315 --> 00:24:04,316
"They say you can hear
a woman crying every night."

679
00:24:04,317 --> 00:24:06,695
- Damn, I hate this.
- Come on.

680
00:24:07,571 --> 00:24:11,115
"It's completely abandoned,
and I got the key."

681
00:24:11,116 --> 00:24:14,326
- So, he gave I-jang's key to King MS?
- Yes.

682
00:24:14,327 --> 00:24:15,578
I guess we need to go there.

683
00:24:15,579 --> 00:24:16,996
It's Baeksudam Garden.

684
00:24:16,997 --> 00:24:17,913
We have to go there.

685
00:24:17,914 --> 00:24:20,583
"There's a strange place near it
where a shaman comes and goes."

686
00:24:20,584 --> 00:24:22,586
- "But that area's off-limits."
- Oh, come on.

687
00:24:24,504 --> 00:24:25,713
"Are you here?"

688
00:24:25,714 --> 00:24:27,298
They spoke on the phone for seven minutes.

689
00:24:27,299 --> 00:24:29,092
- For 7 minutes and 26 seconds.
- It was on June 29th.

690
00:24:29,926 --> 00:24:30,885
KING MS WENT OFF-RADAR ON JULY 1ST

691
00:24:30,886 --> 00:24:32,011
He went off-radar on July 1st.

692
00:24:32,012 --> 00:24:33,429
- He did something.
- He did.

693
00:24:33,430 --> 00:24:35,389
He did something,
and he stopped replying after that.

694
00:24:35,390 --> 00:24:38,434
I think it's like one of those communities

695
00:24:38,435 --> 00:24:40,436
- that investigates haunted houses.
- Oh, right.

696
00:24:40,437 --> 00:24:42,271
- They're specialized experts…
- That's right.

697
00:24:42,272 --> 00:24:44,106
-…who lead the rest of the group.
- Right.

698
00:24:44,107 --> 00:24:48,110
Oh Deok-u handed over a key to King MS.

699
00:24:48,111 --> 00:24:49,571
After that exchange,

700
00:24:50,071 --> 00:24:54,116
King MS fell off the radar,
and then there was a fire.

701
00:24:54,117 --> 00:24:57,620
The village head died soon after.

702
00:24:57,621 --> 00:25:02,374
Oh Deok-u and his parents died
in exactly the same way.

703
00:25:02,375 --> 00:25:06,587
I think the guy they call King MS

704
00:25:06,588 --> 00:25:07,963
is the key.

705
00:25:07,964 --> 00:25:10,257
We need to take the key

706
00:25:10,258 --> 00:25:11,592
- from under the jar stand…
- Yes.

707
00:25:11,593 --> 00:25:13,928
…in I-jang's yard.

708
00:25:13,929 --> 00:25:15,471
Then, let's go to Baeksudam Garden.

709
00:25:15,472 --> 00:25:18,140
- First, let's see his parents' bedroom.
- Good idea.

710
00:25:18,141 --> 00:25:19,391
Let's take a look.

711
00:25:19,392 --> 00:25:20,768
- I'm sweating.
- Me too.

712
00:25:20,769 --> 00:25:21,936
My heart's going to explode.

713
00:25:21,937 --> 00:25:23,687
- I'm so scared.
- Me too.

714
00:25:23,688 --> 00:25:25,732
- Why do I feel so scared today?
- Right?

715
00:25:28,401 --> 00:25:30,362
- Is this the master bedroom?
- Yes, it is.

716
00:25:30,946 --> 00:25:32,364
All the photos are like that.

717
00:25:33,198 --> 00:25:35,950
- Even the family photo…
- They're all the same.

718
00:25:35,951 --> 00:25:37,076
This is terrifying.

719
00:25:37,077 --> 00:25:39,204
- It's all over the bedding.
- It's so chilling.

720
00:25:40,664 --> 00:25:43,332
SEARCHING EVERY CORNER OF THE ROOM

721
00:25:43,333 --> 00:25:45,042
There's nothing special here, is there?

722
00:25:45,043 --> 00:25:46,418
- Is there not?
- If there is…

723
00:25:46,419 --> 00:25:48,128
- You've checked here, right?
- Maybe over there…

724
00:25:48,129 --> 00:25:50,048
THERE ISN'T ANYTHING

725
00:25:50,966 --> 00:25:52,174
- I think we can go.
- Right?

726
00:25:52,175 --> 00:25:53,759
I don't think there are any more clues.

727
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:55,345
I'm so scared.

728
00:26:00,725 --> 00:26:02,269
The phone is ringing.

729
00:26:03,603 --> 00:26:04,729
Someone's calling.

730
00:26:05,564 --> 00:26:06,897
A PHONE CALL MADE TO AN OWNERLESS HOUSE

731
00:26:06,898 --> 00:26:08,232
Breathe.

732
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:09,442
The phone's ringing?

733
00:26:13,822 --> 00:26:15,656
- Do-hoon.
- You do it.

734
00:26:15,657 --> 00:26:16,783
Me?

735
00:26:19,703 --> 00:26:21,329
ELECTED TO PICK UP THE PHONE

736
00:26:22,872 --> 00:26:23,915
Hello?

737
00:26:48,732 --> 00:26:52,902
AGENTS OF MYSTERY SEASON 2

738
00:26:57,157 --> 00:26:58,199
What did you say?

739
00:27:03,830 --> 00:27:06,707
CALLER HANGS UP AFTER LEAVING
A MYSTERIOUS MESSAGE

740
00:27:06,708 --> 00:27:08,167
- What did they say?
- What did they say?

741
00:27:08,168 --> 00:27:10,669
They mumbled something,
then said, "I'll kill them all."

742
00:27:10,670 --> 00:27:13,173
I just heard them say,
"I'll kill them all."

743
00:27:13,673 --> 00:27:14,715
I still have goosebumps.

744
00:27:14,716 --> 00:27:16,091
Look.

745
00:27:16,092 --> 00:27:18,761
It sounded like,
"I'll kill whoever picks up the call."

746
00:27:18,762 --> 00:27:19,678
It's a murder threat?

747
00:27:19,679 --> 00:27:21,013
They'll kill whoever picked up?

748
00:27:21,014 --> 00:27:23,140
- Yes, I just heard "I'll kill them."
- I didn't pick up.

749
00:27:23,141 --> 00:27:25,142
- Me neither.
- I'm the target?

750
00:27:25,143 --> 00:27:26,727
- Me?
- Do-hoon, you can just push them.

751
00:27:26,728 --> 00:27:28,437
I really will push someone.

752
00:27:28,438 --> 00:27:30,856
They might be trying to kill
anyone who investigates.

753
00:27:30,857 --> 00:27:32,274
- Maybe.
- I think so.

754
00:27:32,275 --> 00:27:34,026
- They want to kill us.
- Anyone who investigates…

755
00:27:34,027 --> 00:27:35,611
Who was the caller?

756
00:27:35,612 --> 00:27:36,862
It must be King MS.

757
00:27:36,863 --> 00:27:38,947
Doesn't that say King MS?

758
00:27:38,948 --> 00:27:40,157
It does.

759
00:27:40,158 --> 00:27:42,159
But if he's gone off the radar,

760
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:43,410
isn't he a victim?

761
00:27:43,411 --> 00:27:45,245
- I think so too.
- He could be a victim.

762
00:27:45,246 --> 00:27:46,497
Or he could just not be replying.

763
00:27:46,498 --> 00:27:47,873
- I think that's it.
- Me too.

764
00:27:47,874 --> 00:27:50,334
There might be a third person

765
00:27:50,335 --> 00:27:51,877
who did something to Deok-u and King MS.

766
00:27:51,878 --> 00:27:53,879
Or King MS could be behind it all.

767
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:55,548
We have to catch them.

768
00:27:56,132 --> 00:27:57,216
- Should we go?
- Should we?

769
00:27:57,217 --> 00:27:59,009
Yes, it's getting too dark.

770
00:27:59,010 --> 00:28:00,844
In any case,
I think someone knows we're here.

771
00:28:00,845 --> 00:28:01,887
- Right?
- I think so.

772
00:28:01,888 --> 00:28:05,140
I wish they would just turn a blind eye.

773
00:28:05,141 --> 00:28:06,392
Who?

774
00:28:06,393 --> 00:28:07,936
Whoever it was that called.

775
00:28:19,906 --> 00:28:21,740
I think it was over there on the map.

776
00:28:21,741 --> 00:28:23,033
- Let's head out.
- Should we walk?

777
00:28:23,034 --> 00:28:24,284
- Shall we?
- My heart's pounding.

778
00:28:24,285 --> 00:28:25,994
- Yes, let's walk.
- It's just next door.

779
00:28:25,995 --> 00:28:26,912
That blue roof--

780
00:28:26,913 --> 00:28:28,415
What is that?

781
00:28:29,124 --> 00:28:31,583
- Is that a child?
- That surprised me.

782
00:28:31,584 --> 00:28:35,587
A CHILD IS PLAYING IN FRONT OF THE HOUSE

783
00:28:35,588 --> 00:28:38,340
Hey there, kid.

784
00:28:38,341 --> 00:28:40,092
- Who are you?
- Hello.

785
00:28:40,093 --> 00:28:41,427
- Hello.
- Hello.

786
00:28:41,428 --> 00:28:42,595
Where do you live?

787
00:28:43,263 --> 00:28:44,931
I live over there.

788
00:28:45,432 --> 00:28:47,891
What's your name?

789
00:28:47,892 --> 00:28:48,809
It's Jin-su.

790
00:28:48,810 --> 00:28:50,728
- Jin-su?
- Your name is Jin-su?

791
00:28:50,729 --> 00:28:52,104
What are you doing here?

792
00:28:52,105 --> 00:28:53,856
I'm waiting for my mom.

793
00:28:53,857 --> 00:28:55,315
Where is your mom?

794
00:28:55,316 --> 00:28:56,525
I don't know.

795
00:28:56,526 --> 00:28:58,694
- You don't know?
- When did you last see her?

796
00:28:58,695 --> 00:29:00,280
- I don't know.
- You don't know?

797
00:29:00,989 --> 00:29:01,947
It's a sword.

798
00:29:01,948 --> 00:29:03,031
He has a sword.

799
00:29:03,032 --> 00:29:04,324
Step back, Yong-jin.

800
00:29:04,325 --> 00:29:06,452
I think you should be careful, Yong-jin.

801
00:29:06,453 --> 00:29:07,995
Come here, Yong-jin.

802
00:29:07,996 --> 00:29:09,955
- Just in case.
- Come on, Yong-jin.

803
00:29:09,956 --> 00:29:12,541
Why did they put that in from the start?

804
00:29:12,542 --> 00:29:14,251
It's driving me crazy.

805
00:29:14,252 --> 00:29:16,754
I was worried he might run at me.

806
00:29:16,755 --> 00:29:19,298
Of course, I could easily hold him down.

807
00:29:19,299 --> 00:29:21,216
I have a physical advantage.

808
00:29:21,217 --> 00:29:22,968
Why did they put that in from the start?

809
00:29:22,969 --> 00:29:24,928
I have to go now.

810
00:29:24,929 --> 00:29:26,638
- Okay.
- Bye.

811
00:29:26,639 --> 00:29:28,474
- Take care.
- Where are you going?

812
00:29:28,475 --> 00:29:29,850
- Bye, Jin-su.
- Bye.

813
00:29:29,851 --> 00:29:31,895
- Bye, Jin-su.
- Be careful.

814
00:29:35,857 --> 00:29:38,442
JIN-SU VANISHES INTO THE DISTANCE

815
00:29:38,443 --> 00:29:39,985
My heart can't take this.

816
00:29:39,986 --> 00:29:41,904
I'm so scared.

817
00:29:41,905 --> 00:29:43,071
Why was Jin-su playing here?

818
00:29:43,072 --> 00:29:45,283
- What was he digging?
- Right?

819
00:29:45,867 --> 00:29:48,369
This is a village
of flowing water and warm hearts.

820
00:29:49,078 --> 00:29:51,330
- Oh, you're right.
- Shall we go?

821
00:29:51,331 --> 00:29:52,372
BAEKSUDAM VILLAGE

822
00:29:52,373 --> 00:29:55,042
- That really surprised me.
- Me too.

823
00:29:55,043 --> 00:29:57,127
Maybe Jin-su

824
00:29:57,128 --> 00:29:59,254
- is the start of all this.
- Maybe.

825
00:29:59,255 --> 00:30:00,339
He could be the key.

826
00:30:00,340 --> 00:30:02,634
If they harmed a child, I won't let it go.

827
00:30:03,134 --> 00:30:05,135
Up until that point,

828
00:30:05,136 --> 00:30:09,181
we hadn't seen anyone in the village.

829
00:30:09,182 --> 00:30:11,225
It made us wonder who he was.

830
00:30:11,226 --> 00:30:12,142
WHERE DID JIN-SU COME FROM?

831
00:30:12,143 --> 00:30:14,186
Jin-su kept his eyes on you,
holding his sword, Yong-jin.

832
00:30:14,187 --> 00:30:15,103
He did.

833
00:30:15,104 --> 00:30:16,814
I think you're the main target today.

834
00:30:16,815 --> 00:30:17,856
I'm going to lose my mind.

835
00:30:17,857 --> 00:30:21,152
I think Jin-su will
pull off a great feat today.

836
00:30:21,778 --> 00:30:22,987
But even for me…

837
00:30:23,696 --> 00:30:26,323
Isn't it a bit much to lose to a kid?

838
00:30:26,324 --> 00:30:28,784
How can I lose to Jin-su?

839
00:30:28,785 --> 00:30:30,410
You're a very brave person.

840
00:30:30,411 --> 00:30:32,579
- It's better to lose to a mutant.
- Yes.

841
00:30:32,580 --> 00:30:35,624
- It sucks to think I might lose to Jin-su.
- Of course.

842
00:30:35,625 --> 00:30:37,543
Isn't he around your son's age, Yong-jin?

843
00:30:37,544 --> 00:30:39,212
- Yes, he is.
- He's that young.

844
00:30:40,296 --> 00:30:42,005
- This is the place.
- What is this?

845
00:30:42,006 --> 00:30:43,173
We're here.

846
00:30:43,174 --> 00:30:47,886
SCENE OF THE FIRST INCIDENT

847
00:30:47,887 --> 00:30:50,931
"They found the village head and his wife
dead in their home."

848
00:30:50,932 --> 00:30:52,267
<i>- Oh, no.
- That was yesterday.</i>

849
00:30:52,892 --> 00:30:57,396
THE VILLAGE HEAD I-JANG'S HOUSE
AS PICTURED IN THE REPORT

850
00:30:57,397 --> 00:30:59,148
It's so eerie here.

851
00:30:59,774 --> 00:31:01,734
What is that?

852
00:31:02,527 --> 00:31:03,902
- Oh, that's…
- It's that place.

853
00:31:03,903 --> 00:31:05,488
- It's the Prosperity Hall.
- It's the hall.

854
00:31:07,073 --> 00:31:08,532
Why is the hall so big?

855
00:31:08,533 --> 00:31:09,908
THE PROSPERITY HALL IS
AT THE END OF THE ALLEY

856
00:31:09,909 --> 00:31:13,036
We need to look under the jar stand.

857
00:31:13,037 --> 00:31:14,998
- We need to get the key.
- It's his house key.

858
00:31:16,207 --> 00:31:17,165
It's not here.

859
00:31:17,166 --> 00:31:19,042
- There's a cat.
- It must be in there.

860
00:31:19,043 --> 00:31:19,960
Why is it here?

861
00:31:19,961 --> 00:31:21,712
- Look at the cats.
- Oh, they're kittens.

862
00:31:21,713 --> 00:31:23,589
They're so cute.

863
00:31:23,590 --> 00:31:24,841
Come on in.

864
00:31:26,092 --> 00:31:27,468
Come on in.

865
00:31:28,678 --> 00:31:31,806
GABEE HEADS TOWARDS THE JAR STANDS

866
00:31:33,516 --> 00:31:34,642
- I found it.
- It's there?

867
00:31:36,603 --> 00:31:38,688
- Let's go in.
- It's the house key.

868
00:31:39,272 --> 00:31:40,439
GLANCING AT THE SKY

869
00:31:40,440 --> 00:31:42,024
- Even the birds sound scary.
- They do.

870
00:31:42,025 --> 00:31:44,401
THE SKY IS UNUSUALLY BLEAK

871
00:31:44,402 --> 00:31:46,653
It feels like the film <i>The Wailing.</i>

872
00:31:46,654 --> 00:31:48,196
- I thought the same.
- It does.

873
00:31:48,197 --> 00:31:49,407
I'm scared.

874
00:31:50,867 --> 00:31:51,743
LET'S GO IN

875
00:31:52,577 --> 00:31:54,536
BRAVELY ENTERING I-JANG'S HOUSE

876
00:31:54,537 --> 00:31:55,538
The lights…

877
00:31:56,080 --> 00:31:57,372
- I can't see anything.
- It's so dark.

878
00:31:57,373 --> 00:31:58,498
Yes, come in.

879
00:31:58,499 --> 00:31:59,918
Isn't there a light switch?

880
00:32:01,461 --> 00:32:03,378
- We need to find a light.
- What if someone's here?

881
00:32:03,379 --> 00:32:04,964
I'll die if there is.

882
00:32:05,590 --> 00:32:06,757
I mean it.

883
00:32:06,758 --> 00:32:07,925
Karina says she'll die.

884
00:32:07,926 --> 00:32:09,718
- You need to take care of me.
- You'll die? Wait.

885
00:32:09,719 --> 00:32:11,261
I'll handle it for you.

886
00:32:11,262 --> 00:32:12,804
You found it!

887
00:32:12,805 --> 00:32:14,766
It's here.

888
00:32:15,391 --> 00:32:16,725
- It's the fluid.
- It's everywhere.

889
00:32:16,726 --> 00:32:18,894
There's more here than in the other house.

890
00:32:18,895 --> 00:32:20,812
The houses were in a similar state.

891
00:32:20,813 --> 00:32:22,189
The black fluid was everywhere.

892
00:32:22,190 --> 00:32:23,482
- Look.
- It's all over.

893
00:32:23,483 --> 00:32:25,318
- There's something here.
- There is.

894
00:32:26,110 --> 00:32:29,446
We found documents on the table.

895
00:32:29,447 --> 00:32:31,698
THE VILLAGE HEAD'S NOTEPAD
AND A LOOSE PIECE OF PAPER

896
00:32:31,699 --> 00:32:33,659
- This is just a news article.
- Okay.

897
00:32:33,660 --> 00:32:35,369
It's about the fire
at the Prosperity Hall.

898
00:32:35,370 --> 00:32:37,245
BODIES FOUND WHILE PUTTING OUT FIRE
AT PROSPERITY HALL

899
00:32:37,246 --> 00:32:40,458
<i>It also contained a village map.</i>

900
00:32:41,042 --> 00:32:43,293
Let's see where we are.

901
00:32:43,294 --> 00:32:44,503
We're here, right?

902
00:32:44,504 --> 00:32:46,838
And we need to head to Baeksudam Garden.

903
00:32:46,839 --> 00:32:47,756
It's far away.

904
00:32:47,757 --> 00:32:49,716
- It is quite far.
- That's far.

905
00:32:49,717 --> 00:32:50,969
But we need to go there first.

906
00:32:51,511 --> 00:32:54,012
- You mean the other house?
- I mean Prosperity Hall.

907
00:32:54,013 --> 00:32:54,930
We need to go there.

908
00:32:54,931 --> 00:32:56,682
- This is where the hall is.
- Yes.

909
00:32:56,683 --> 00:32:58,266
Yes, that's where the fire was.

910
00:32:58,267 --> 00:33:01,269
- Is there any new information?
- Here.

911
00:33:01,270 --> 00:33:03,271
"Prosperity Hall Operating Rules."

912
00:33:03,272 --> 00:33:05,691
"Meet on Mondays once every two weeks."

913
00:33:05,692 --> 00:33:08,151
"Monthly membership fee
is 10,000 won per person."

914
00:33:08,152 --> 00:33:11,822
I think this is a log
of the money that was collected.

915
00:33:11,823 --> 00:33:13,657
Some people are marked as exempt.

916
00:33:13,658 --> 00:33:16,827
Shin Nae-ryeong was
given a free pass every month.

917
00:33:16,828 --> 00:33:17,953
But they wrote,

918
00:33:17,954 --> 00:33:19,579
"How long should she get
special treatment?"

919
00:33:19,580 --> 00:33:20,539
They weren't pleased.

920
00:33:20,540 --> 00:33:21,456
Shin Nae-ryeong?

921
00:33:21,457 --> 00:33:23,000
- Was she a shaman?
- It seems like it.

922
00:33:23,001 --> 00:33:24,251
- Oh, you're right.
- It makes sense.

923
00:33:24,252 --> 00:33:25,502
It sounds like <i>shin naerim.</i>

924
00:33:25,503 --> 00:33:27,796
- They said a shaman came by a lot.
- They did.

925
00:33:27,797 --> 00:33:30,507
"There's a strange place near it
where a shaman comes and goes."

926
00:33:30,508 --> 00:33:32,801
- "But that area's off-limits."
- Oh, come on.

927
00:33:32,802 --> 00:33:34,845
Her name sounded like <i>shin naerim,</i>

928
00:33:34,846 --> 00:33:36,138
which means "spirit possession."

929
00:33:36,139 --> 00:33:38,932
So, we thought she could be a shaman.

930
00:33:38,933 --> 00:33:41,101
Once every five years,

931
00:33:41,102 --> 00:33:43,562
- they held some kind of festival.
- It feels suspicious.

932
00:33:43,563 --> 00:33:47,441
This year, they were set
on developing Baeksudam Garden.

933
00:33:47,442 --> 00:33:48,817
That was the June agenda.

934
00:33:48,818 --> 00:33:50,277
- They planned to develop it?
- Yes.

935
00:33:50,278 --> 00:33:51,778
So, it's a redevelopment.

936
00:33:51,779 --> 00:33:54,157
It says they needed
to persuade opposing residents.

937
00:33:54,866 --> 00:33:57,743
- Opposing residents?
- Shin Nae-ryeong was one of them.

938
00:33:57,744 --> 00:34:01,663
They won over all the opposing residents

939
00:34:01,664 --> 00:34:04,082
except for Shin Nae-ryeong.

940
00:34:04,083 --> 00:34:05,751
Shin Nae-ryeong was the only one

941
00:34:05,752 --> 00:34:08,795
who was not persuaded in the end.

942
00:34:08,796 --> 00:34:11,631
So, we started to wonder

943
00:34:11,632 --> 00:34:14,134
why she opposed it to the very end.

944
00:34:14,135 --> 00:34:17,180
"Why is she so against it?
Does she want money?"

945
00:34:19,307 --> 00:34:20,766
"As if she could curse us."

946
00:34:20,767 --> 00:34:22,934
- So, Shin Nae-ryeong…
- She must have cursed them!

947
00:34:22,935 --> 00:34:25,062
- No, I think Shin Nae-ryeong…
- Yes?

948
00:34:25,063 --> 00:34:27,606
-…knew it was a bad idea.
- I see.

949
00:34:27,607 --> 00:34:28,982
- She knew it was risky.
- Right.

950
00:34:28,983 --> 00:34:31,610
She warned them against it.

951
00:34:31,611 --> 00:34:33,195
If they did it, they would be cursed.

952
00:34:33,196 --> 00:34:35,572
And that's basically what happened.

953
00:34:35,573 --> 00:34:37,074
- Right.
- That makes sense.

954
00:34:37,075 --> 00:34:39,868
Shin Nae-ryeong might
know what the black fluid is.

955
00:34:39,869 --> 00:34:41,995
- It makes sense.
- I think we need to meet her.

956
00:34:41,996 --> 00:34:44,706
- She must have a reason for opposing.
- I agree.

957
00:34:44,707 --> 00:34:46,124
Let's go in there.

958
00:34:46,125 --> 00:34:47,293
ENTERING THE MASTER BEDROOM WITH QUESTIONS

959
00:34:53,633 --> 00:34:57,678
THE MASTER BEDROOM
IS ALSO COVERED IN BLACK FLUID

960
00:34:58,930 --> 00:35:00,472
The reservoir area

961
00:35:00,473 --> 00:35:03,308
was the focus
of the redevelopment project.

962
00:35:03,309 --> 00:35:06,853
They were going to redevelop
the reservoir area,

963
00:35:06,854 --> 00:35:09,564
but Shin Nae-ryeong was against the idea.

964
00:35:09,565 --> 00:35:13,735
Baeksudam is the name
of the village reservoir.

965
00:35:13,736 --> 00:35:18,115
They were planning to redevelop that area.

966
00:35:18,116 --> 00:35:20,075
It reminds me of a book I read.

967
00:35:20,076 --> 00:35:22,869
A village planned
to redevelop the local reservoir,

968
00:35:22,870 --> 00:35:25,247
when the village was
suddenly flooded by heavy rain.

969
00:35:25,248 --> 00:35:26,706
There are many stories like that.

970
00:35:26,707 --> 00:35:30,001
So, I wonder if Shin Nae-ryeong knew…

971
00:35:30,002 --> 00:35:31,378
- She predicted that would happen?
- Yes.

972
00:35:31,379 --> 00:35:33,213
So, that's why she opposed.

973
00:35:33,214 --> 00:35:35,048
Is the reservoir haunted by angry spirits?

974
00:35:35,049 --> 00:35:35,966
- Yes.
- Yes.

975
00:35:35,967 --> 00:35:38,009
We definitely have to investigate her.

976
00:35:38,010 --> 00:35:39,094
Where is she now?

977
00:35:39,095 --> 00:35:40,929
Won't she be near the hall?

978
00:35:40,930 --> 00:35:41,931
Let's make our way there.

979
00:35:42,807 --> 00:35:44,517
I'm really scared.

980
00:35:46,435 --> 00:35:48,020
Should we take the back scratcher?

981
00:35:48,563 --> 00:35:49,938
Let's take something.

982
00:35:49,939 --> 00:35:52,232
You feel safer holding onto something.

983
00:35:52,233 --> 00:35:54,651
- John, I feel like today's mission…
- Yes?

984
00:35:54,652 --> 00:35:58,156
…is not about solving a puzzle
to get to the next stage.

985
00:36:02,326 --> 00:36:03,618
BLACK FLUID FLOWS FROM THE TAP

986
00:36:03,619 --> 00:36:05,371
- What is it?
- The water…

987
00:36:11,127 --> 00:36:12,169
SHOCKED

988
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:14,546
It must be water from the reservoir.

989
00:36:14,547 --> 00:36:16,423
That's crazy. How can the water be black?

990
00:36:16,424 --> 00:36:18,175
- That's crazy.
- I can't turn off the tap.

991
00:36:18,176 --> 00:36:19,551
Is it the same here?

992
00:36:19,552 --> 00:36:21,261
It's coming out from here too.

993
00:36:21,262 --> 00:36:22,179
It's here too?

994
00:36:22,180 --> 00:36:23,722
- Yes.
- It's everywhere.

995
00:36:23,723 --> 00:36:24,681
BLACK FLUID FLOWS IN THE BATHROOM

996
00:36:24,682 --> 00:36:27,809
Black fluid was flowing
from all the sinks in the house,

997
00:36:27,810 --> 00:36:30,104
in both the kitchen and the bathroom.

998
00:36:30,605 --> 00:36:33,607
We thought the fluid could be dangerous.

999
00:36:33,608 --> 00:36:36,902
We all had the same instinct.

1000
00:36:36,903 --> 00:36:38,987
We knew the fluid was dangerous.

1001
00:36:38,988 --> 00:36:40,822
- Isn't it dangerous?
- Shouldn't we head to the hall?

1002
00:36:40,823 --> 00:36:42,950
Let's get going.

1003
00:36:43,951 --> 00:36:45,493
Mom!

1004
00:36:45,494 --> 00:36:46,787
WHAT IS THAT?

1005
00:36:47,538 --> 00:36:49,331
- Is that Jin-su?
- Jin-su?

1006
00:36:49,332 --> 00:36:51,124
- Jin-su?
- Wasn't it a child's voice?

1007
00:36:51,125 --> 00:36:52,543
Jin-su's here?

1008
00:36:53,461 --> 00:36:55,295
- Jin-su?
- He cried for his mom.

1009
00:36:55,296 --> 00:36:56,880
- Jin-su?
- Are you there?

1010
00:36:56,881 --> 00:36:58,590
DESPERATELY CALLING OUT TO JIN-SU

1011
00:36:58,591 --> 00:36:59,841
I definitely heard him.

1012
00:36:59,842 --> 00:37:00,801
Right?

1013
00:37:01,344 --> 00:37:02,260
I'm so scared.

1014
00:37:02,261 --> 00:37:03,637
- There's Jin-su!
- Mom!

1015
00:37:03,638 --> 00:37:04,804
- Hey, Jin-su!
- Jin-su!

1016
00:37:04,805 --> 00:37:06,306
- Where is he?
- He's over there.

1017
00:37:06,307 --> 00:37:07,683
- Jin-su.
- Let's go to him.

1018
00:37:08,851 --> 00:37:09,809
Mom!

1019
00:37:09,810 --> 00:37:11,811
There's a group of strange men and women.

1020
00:37:11,812 --> 00:37:14,189
They're following me around!

1021
00:37:14,190 --> 00:37:16,024
He's talking about us.

1022
00:37:16,025 --> 00:37:17,651
- He left his sword.
- He threw it down.

1023
00:37:17,652 --> 00:37:19,487
- He did? Where is it?
- It's on the floor.

1024
00:37:20,988 --> 00:37:22,823
- Let's head over.
- Let's check it out.

1025
00:37:23,407 --> 00:37:26,159
Is he leading us into a trap?

1026
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:28,536
I feel like it's dangerous to go in.

1027
00:37:28,537 --> 00:37:29,955
But we have no choice…

1028
00:37:29,956 --> 00:37:31,623
- We have to go in.
- I know.

1029
00:37:31,624 --> 00:37:34,042
I'll get the sword.

1030
00:37:34,043 --> 00:37:36,003
- Yong-jin, you need to stay away.
- I'm okay.

1031
00:37:37,088 --> 00:37:40,215
PICKING UP JIN-SU'S WOODEN SWORD

1032
00:37:40,216 --> 00:37:41,716
Is it okay for you to hold it?

1033
00:37:41,717 --> 00:37:44,010
- You need to keep away from it.
- She's right.

1034
00:37:44,011 --> 00:37:45,428
- Give it to me.
- Let her take it.

1035
00:37:45,429 --> 00:37:46,513
I'll hold onto it.

1036
00:37:46,514 --> 00:37:47,430
Will you hold it, Gabee?

1037
00:37:47,431 --> 00:37:50,016
It feels even eerier
because it's a full moon tonight.

1038
00:37:50,017 --> 00:37:51,518
- Right?
- This is driving me crazy.

1039
00:37:51,519 --> 00:37:55,356
PERFECT DARKNESS HAS
FALLEN ON BAEKSUDAM VILLAGE

1040
00:37:56,732 --> 00:37:58,525
I'm too scared to go in alone.

1041
00:37:58,526 --> 00:38:00,653
We need to enter here, right?

1042
00:38:01,445 --> 00:38:04,781
THE NEXT LOCATION

1043
00:38:04,782 --> 00:38:07,784
I think we need to brace ourselves.

1044
00:38:07,785 --> 00:38:08,828
THE BURNED-DOWN VILLAGE PROSPERITY HALL

1045
00:38:09,495 --> 00:38:11,204
- This is where the fire was.
- Yes.

1046
00:38:11,205 --> 00:38:12,497
This is the Prosperity Hall.

1047
00:38:12,498 --> 00:38:13,790
You can still smell it.

1048
00:38:13,791 --> 00:38:15,543
- It smells of smoke.
- It does.

1049
00:38:16,294 --> 00:38:17,669
- It smells burnt.
- It does.

1050
00:38:17,670 --> 00:38:19,672
- It's very strong.
- It is.

1051
00:38:20,881 --> 00:38:26,177
THE BURNED-DOWN PROSPERITY HALL

1052
00:38:26,178 --> 00:38:28,888
<i>You could still smell the smoke,</i>

1053
00:38:28,889 --> 00:38:32,184
<i>and it all felt very creepy.</i>

1054
00:38:33,436 --> 00:38:34,561
My heart's pounding.

1055
00:38:34,562 --> 00:38:35,730
I think I'm going to be sick.

1056
00:38:36,355 --> 00:38:39,149
John, I'm so scared
that I don't know what to do.

1057
00:38:39,150 --> 00:38:42,944
Did the fire start when King MS arrived?

1058
00:38:42,945 --> 00:38:46,781
They weren't sure if he caused it or not.

1059
00:38:46,782 --> 00:38:49,826
Did King MS cause all the events?

1060
00:38:49,827 --> 00:38:52,829
We had to figure that out first.

1061
00:38:52,830 --> 00:38:55,081
FINDS SOMETHING

1062
00:38:55,082 --> 00:38:56,458
This cabinet is locked.

1063
00:38:56,459 --> 00:38:58,085
- We need a passcode.
- Okay.

1064
00:38:58,961 --> 00:39:01,714
IT'S LOCKED WITH A 4-DIGIT PADLOCK

1065
00:39:03,049 --> 00:39:04,132
What is that?

1066
00:39:04,133 --> 00:39:06,968
A CREEPY NOISE IS COMING FROM THE CABINET

1067
00:39:06,969 --> 00:39:08,721
There's a noise coming from inside.

1068
00:39:11,474 --> 00:39:12,725
I don't think we should open it.

1069
00:39:13,726 --> 00:39:14,977
- This is too scary.
- Right?

1070
00:39:15,561 --> 00:39:18,646
I'm sorry.
I don't think we can let you out.

1071
00:39:18,647 --> 00:39:20,648
- Karina, I'm more scared than ever.
- Gabee.

1072
00:39:20,649 --> 00:39:22,026
- Should we hug?
- Yes.

1073
00:39:22,526 --> 00:39:25,070
This is the scariest mission so far.

1074
00:39:25,071 --> 00:39:27,280
I'm too scared to do anything.

1075
00:39:27,281 --> 00:39:28,573
I'm too scared to touch anything.

1076
00:39:28,574 --> 00:39:30,033
What do we do?

1077
00:39:30,034 --> 00:39:32,077
Is it okay to open this?

1078
00:39:32,078 --> 00:39:34,830
We can hear a strange noise inside it.

1079
00:39:38,793 --> 00:39:41,086
I'm too scared to move.

1080
00:39:41,087 --> 00:39:43,506
NERVOUS WRECKS

1081
00:39:44,090 --> 00:39:45,507
What else is there?

1082
00:39:45,508 --> 00:39:46,467
AND ONE FEARLESS AGENT

1083
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:58,895
<i>I found a photo that showed
the opening date of Prosperity Hall.</i>

1084
00:39:58,896 --> 00:40:01,022
The Prosperity Hall opened on March 15th.

1085
00:40:01,023 --> 00:40:02,148
- March 15th?
- March 15th?

1086
00:40:02,149 --> 00:40:05,276
OPENING DATE: MARCH 15TH, 1975

1087
00:40:05,277 --> 00:40:06,361
Should we try 0315?

1088
00:40:06,362 --> 00:40:07,321
Let's try it.

1089
00:40:09,198 --> 00:40:12,826
ENTERING THE OPENING DATE AS THE PASSCODE

1090
00:40:12,827 --> 00:40:13,952
Be careful.

1091
00:40:13,953 --> 00:40:15,453
- Watch your hand.
- Is it working?

1092
00:40:15,454 --> 00:40:16,830
No, that's not it.

1093
00:40:16,831 --> 00:40:18,665
Could it be 1975?

1094
00:40:18,666 --> 00:40:20,083
I'll try it.

1095
00:40:20,084 --> 00:40:22,128
2ND ATTEMPT

1096
00:40:24,797 --> 00:40:25,713
It worked.

1097
00:40:25,714 --> 00:40:26,965
- It worked?
- What was it?

1098
00:40:26,966 --> 00:40:28,174
- It was 1975.
- It's 1975.

1099
00:40:28,175 --> 00:40:29,384
IT ONLY TOOK TWO TRIES

1100
00:40:29,385 --> 00:40:30,760
- Be careful.
- Wait a minute.

1101
00:40:30,761 --> 00:40:31,719
TIME TO OPEN IT

1102
00:40:31,720 --> 00:40:33,304
- I'll open it.
- Let's stick together.

1103
00:40:33,305 --> 00:40:35,224
- Watch your hands.
- We need to overcome our fear.

1104
00:40:39,437 --> 00:40:40,770
What is that?

1105
00:40:40,771 --> 00:40:42,814
- What is all this?
- What is it?

1106
00:40:42,815 --> 00:40:45,442
OBJECTS INSIDE THE CABINET
SPARED FROM THE FIRE

1107
00:40:45,443 --> 00:40:47,235
BEGINNING THE SEARCH

1108
00:40:47,236 --> 00:40:48,404
Let's check it out.

1109
00:40:48,946 --> 00:40:52,115
Were they for the festival's opening?

1110
00:40:52,116 --> 00:40:54,742
Baeksudam Village won an award.

1111
00:40:54,743 --> 00:40:56,161
- Really?
- Yes.

1112
00:40:56,162 --> 00:40:57,787
Baeksudam Village took part

1113
00:40:57,788 --> 00:41:00,999
- in a water taste-reviving contest.
- They did.

1114
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:02,750
- They won an award for it.
- That's right.

1115
00:41:02,751 --> 00:41:06,004
This black fluid is a big deal.

1116
00:41:06,005 --> 00:41:08,590
- It's a huge threat.
- It is a big problem.

1117
00:41:08,591 --> 00:41:10,300
If the village was famous for its water,

1118
00:41:10,301 --> 00:41:12,177
it's a big deal
that the water's turned black.

1119
00:41:12,178 --> 00:41:13,095
It is.

1120
00:41:16,849 --> 00:41:19,267
"Local Legends of Yanggok."

1121
00:41:19,268 --> 00:41:22,395
<i>There was a booklet
and a pamphlet that was titled</i>

1122
00:41:22,396 --> 00:41:24,063
<i>"Folk Culture Festival."</i>

1123
00:41:24,064 --> 00:41:26,232
Once every five years,

1124
00:41:26,233 --> 00:41:28,568
- they held some kind of festival.
- It feels suspicious.

1125
00:41:28,569 --> 00:41:34,115
The Folk Culture Festival
was first created by Shin Nae-ryeong.

1126
00:41:34,116 --> 00:41:35,783
- We were right!
- She created it.

1127
00:41:35,784 --> 00:41:36,743
We were right about her.

1128
00:41:36,744 --> 00:41:39,662
She's a third-generation shaman.

1129
00:41:39,663 --> 00:41:41,080
- She is a shaman.
- Yes.

1130
00:41:41,081 --> 00:41:44,250
- She first performed the Baeksuje Ritual.
- Okay.

1131
00:41:44,251 --> 00:41:47,420
<i>She opposed the redevelopment.</i>

1132
00:41:47,421 --> 00:41:50,840
There must've been a supernatural reason.

1133
00:41:50,841 --> 00:41:54,427
"It's a century-old ritual
unique to Baeksudam."

1134
00:41:54,428 --> 00:41:58,556
"It's been performed
by generations of hereditary shamans."

1135
00:41:58,557 --> 00:41:59,974
What date is the festival?

1136
00:41:59,975 --> 00:42:01,059
It's written here.

1137
00:42:01,060 --> 00:42:03,895
It first took place on July 4th, 2020.

1138
00:42:03,896 --> 00:42:05,396
- July 4th?
- They held it then.

1139
00:42:05,397 --> 00:42:07,774
- It must be an annual festival.
- Didn't they die on July 4th?

1140
00:42:07,775 --> 00:42:09,151
- They did.
- You're right.

1141
00:42:10,277 --> 00:42:11,194
I got chills.

1142
00:42:11,195 --> 00:42:15,740
The village head died on July 4th, 2025.

1143
00:42:15,741 --> 00:42:19,285
<i>He died on the day
they were to hold the Baeksuje Ritual.</i>

1144
00:42:19,286 --> 00:42:22,288
Maybe the reason they died

1145
00:42:22,289 --> 00:42:25,166
<i>was because the ritual
wasn't properly performed.</i>

1146
00:42:25,167 --> 00:42:28,503
Shin Nae-ryeong is clearly a key figure.

1147
00:42:28,504 --> 00:42:29,546
CONTENT LIST

1148
00:42:29,547 --> 00:42:31,965
It says, "The Secret of Baeksudam."

1149
00:42:31,966 --> 00:42:33,841
- It's on page 18.
- Page 18?

1150
00:42:33,842 --> 00:42:35,051
There was a content list.

1151
00:42:35,052 --> 00:42:37,804
One was titled "The Secret of Baeksudam."

1152
00:42:37,805 --> 00:42:40,056
We flipped to that page.

1153
00:42:40,057 --> 00:42:41,933
There was a collection of folktales.

1154
00:42:41,934 --> 00:42:45,687
It contained several tales
of different villages.

1155
00:42:45,688 --> 00:42:49,148
One tale was about Baeksudam Village.

1156
00:42:49,149 --> 00:42:51,693
<i>The secret of Baeksudam</i>

1157
00:42:51,694 --> 00:42:53,653
<i>goes back a hundred years.</i>

1158
00:42:53,654 --> 00:42:55,321
"A hundred years ago,

1159
00:42:55,322 --> 00:42:57,865
there was a quiet village
of flowing water and warm hearts."

1160
00:42:57,866 --> 00:42:59,742
"At the heart of it was a reservoir."

1161
00:42:59,743 --> 00:43:02,537
<i>"It was said to be the meeting point
of a hundred streams."</i>

1162
00:43:02,538 --> 00:43:04,330
<i>"So, it was called Baeksudam Village."</i>

1163
00:43:04,331 --> 00:43:06,416
"On the very outskirts of the village,

1164
00:43:06,417 --> 00:43:08,001
there lived a mother and son."

1165
00:43:08,002 --> 00:43:10,795
"The father had
passed away early from an illness."

1166
00:43:10,796 --> 00:43:14,007
"The mother struggled
to make a living by sewing."

1167
00:43:14,008 --> 00:43:17,635
"One day, a cruel plague
descended on the village."

1168
00:43:17,636 --> 00:43:19,429
"It struck everyone, old and young."

1169
00:43:19,430 --> 00:43:21,014
"And they all died on the spot."

1170
00:43:21,015 --> 00:43:23,641
"Famous doctors were summoned
from nearby villages,

1171
00:43:23,642 --> 00:43:24,934
but they could do nothing to help."

1172
00:43:24,935 --> 00:43:27,770
"The plague could not even be stopped

1173
00:43:27,771 --> 00:43:29,355
by the shaman's
grand sacrificial offerings."

1174
00:43:29,356 --> 00:43:31,399
"The shaman retreated to a dark cave."

1175
00:43:31,400 --> 00:43:33,901
"After praying for seven days and nights,
she received a revelation."

1176
00:43:33,902 --> 00:43:36,738
"A child's strong water energy
clashes with the energy of the reservoir."

1177
00:43:36,739 --> 00:43:40,116
"You must sacrifice the child
in the reservoir to banish the plague."

1178
00:43:40,117 --> 00:43:41,993
- That's crazy!
- That means Jin-su…

1179
00:43:41,994 --> 00:43:43,661
"She remembered
the child on the outskirts."

1180
00:43:43,662 --> 00:43:45,371
"He was born on a day
with strong water energy."

1181
00:43:45,372 --> 00:43:47,206
That poor child.

1182
00:43:47,207 --> 00:43:48,249
I can't believe this.

1183
00:43:48,250 --> 00:43:49,917
Wait a minute.

1184
00:43:49,918 --> 00:43:53,129
That means Jin-su is an apparition.

1185
00:43:53,130 --> 00:43:54,297
- He's a ghost.
- Right.

1186
00:43:54,298 --> 00:43:55,214
He's a ghost?

1187
00:43:55,215 --> 00:43:57,551
<i>- That's scary.
- He was sacrificed.</i>

1188
00:43:59,136 --> 00:44:01,721
<i>When we realized Jin-su
could be the sacrificed child,</i>

1189
00:44:01,722 --> 00:44:03,640
I got goosebumps again.

1190
00:44:03,641 --> 00:44:04,725
Can you see?

1191
00:44:05,351 --> 00:44:06,351
Oh, my gosh.

1192
00:44:06,352 --> 00:44:08,019
- Keep reading.
- "When the child was asleep,

1193
00:44:08,020 --> 00:44:10,021
she wrapped him in a cloth
and gently put him in a jar."

1194
00:44:10,022 --> 00:44:12,357
"The young men of the village set sail

1195
00:44:12,358 --> 00:44:15,068
- with the jar loaded on the boat."
- Oh, gosh.

1196
00:44:15,069 --> 00:44:17,612
"There was a swirling whirlpool
at the deepest point,

1197
00:44:17,613 --> 00:44:19,405
as if the spirits
were demanding a sacrifice."

1198
00:44:19,406 --> 00:44:21,282
"The young men lifted the jar up high."

1199
00:44:21,283 --> 00:44:22,200
"Just then,

1200
00:44:22,201 --> 00:44:25,078
the child in the jar woke up
and began to cry."

1201
00:44:25,079 --> 00:44:27,872
"His little face poked out of the jar
and was filled with terror."

1202
00:44:27,873 --> 00:44:30,583
"The young men could not look at him."

1203
00:44:30,584 --> 00:44:31,793
"They turned their heads away,

1204
00:44:31,794 --> 00:44:34,962
and pushed the child back into the jar."

1205
00:44:34,963 --> 00:44:36,089
"Splash."

1206
00:44:36,090 --> 00:44:37,757
He didn't know where his mom was.

1207
00:44:37,758 --> 00:44:40,635
"His mother ran around
with loose hair, cuts on her bare feet,

1208
00:44:40,636 --> 00:44:42,178
and clothes torn by branches."

1209
00:44:42,179 --> 00:44:46,557
"An old woman took pity on her and tutted,

1210
00:44:46,558 --> 00:44:48,893
'She has no idea her child is
in the cold water.'"

1211
00:44:48,894 --> 00:44:50,228
"So, the mother responded…"

1212
00:44:50,229 --> 00:44:51,187
"I'll kill them all,

1213
00:44:51,188 --> 00:44:52,523
- just like they killed my son."
- Hey!

1214
00:44:53,482 --> 00:44:55,942
The phone call earlier…

1215
00:44:55,943 --> 00:44:59,529
<i>I'm going to kill every bastard
who killed my child.</i>

1216
00:44:59,530 --> 00:45:01,156
<i>I'll kill them all!</i>

1217
00:45:01,740 --> 00:45:03,741
The mother walked into the reservoir

1218
00:45:03,742 --> 00:45:06,452
- to look for her child.
- Right.

1219
00:45:06,453 --> 00:45:08,955
- They both died in the end.
- Right.

1220
00:45:08,956 --> 00:45:10,581
"From then on, the villagers believed

1221
00:45:10,582 --> 00:45:12,208
that they had to appease
the mother's spirit

1222
00:45:12,209 --> 00:45:14,669
or a curse would
spread through the village by water."

1223
00:45:14,670 --> 00:45:16,254
- This explains the black fluid.
- Yes.

1224
00:45:16,255 --> 00:45:17,672
- That's the curse.
- Right.

1225
00:45:17,673 --> 00:45:19,757
"To this day, Baeksudam Village

1226
00:45:19,758 --> 00:45:21,592
performs the Baeksuje Ritual
every five years."

1227
00:45:21,593 --> 00:45:23,678
It could be just a story,

1228
00:45:23,679 --> 00:45:26,597
but it could also be
a legend based on truth.

1229
00:45:26,598 --> 00:45:27,974
That could be the reason

1230
00:45:27,975 --> 00:45:32,228
for all the bad things
that are happening in the village.

1231
00:45:32,229 --> 00:45:34,021
Do we need to break the curse?

1232
00:45:34,022 --> 00:45:35,982
Do we need to hold a ritual?

1233
00:45:35,983 --> 00:45:37,734
We have to perform the ritual?

1234
00:45:37,735 --> 00:45:39,569
We need to find Shin Nae-ryeong

1235
00:45:39,570 --> 00:45:41,738
and ask her what we should do.

1236
00:45:41,739 --> 00:45:43,489
Should we head over there?

1237
00:45:43,490 --> 00:45:44,615
It was a hundred years ago.

1238
00:45:44,616 --> 00:45:46,284
- Yes.
- My head hurts.

1239
00:45:46,285 --> 00:45:49,328
We have the Yonghandang Shrine address.
Should we head to the car?

1240
00:45:49,329 --> 00:45:52,290
Now we understand what's happening.

1241
00:45:52,291 --> 00:45:54,250
So, a hundred years ago,

1242
00:45:54,251 --> 00:45:56,377
- Jin-su was sacrificed.
- Yes, he was.

1243
00:45:56,378 --> 00:45:58,421
Come to think of it,

1244
00:45:58,422 --> 00:46:00,339
did you notice Jin-su's shoes?

1245
00:46:00,340 --> 00:46:01,674
- They were from the past.
- It was.

1246
00:46:01,675 --> 00:46:03,468
- They were very old-fashioned.
- Right.

1247
00:46:03,469 --> 00:46:05,720
And kids nowadays
don't play with things like this.

1248
00:46:05,721 --> 00:46:08,055
Jin-su is technically older than us.

1249
00:46:08,056 --> 00:46:08,973
He is.

1250
00:46:08,974 --> 00:46:10,975
Why did he have a wooden sword?

1251
00:46:10,976 --> 00:46:13,561
It's the only thing kids had
to play with back then.

1252
00:46:13,562 --> 00:46:14,520
I feel so sorry for him.

1253
00:46:14,521 --> 00:46:16,398
Should we leave the wooden sword?

1254
00:46:16,899 --> 00:46:18,065
- It's Jin-su's.
- Keep it for now.

1255
00:46:18,066 --> 00:46:19,485
- We might see him again.
- Okay.

1256
00:46:20,736 --> 00:46:22,153
- We might see him again.
- Okay.

1257
00:46:22,154 --> 00:46:25,907
A WOODEN SIGN SUDDENLY FELL

1258
00:46:25,908 --> 00:46:27,325
- What happened?
- I don't know.

1259
00:46:27,326 --> 00:46:28,701
Hurry, come here.

1260
00:46:28,702 --> 00:46:31,078
- What is it?
- Something's exploding.

1261
00:46:31,079 --> 00:46:32,705
- What's happening?
- It's the curse.

1262
00:46:32,706 --> 00:46:34,081
It's on fire.

1263
00:46:34,082 --> 00:46:35,249
What on earth?

1264
00:46:35,250 --> 00:46:37,044
- It's burning.
- The sign fell down.

1265
00:46:37,669 --> 00:46:40,505
<i>It was very eerie
because everywhere we went,</i>

1266
00:46:40,506 --> 00:46:43,424
the place seemed to be haunted.

1267
00:46:43,425 --> 00:46:46,594
It was as if an angry spirit
was trying to warn us

1268
00:46:46,595 --> 00:46:49,430
that we needed to stop
and leave them alone.

1269
00:46:49,431 --> 00:46:50,723
Let's go!

1270
00:46:50,724 --> 00:46:52,475
I hate this story the most.

1271
00:46:52,476 --> 00:46:54,310
How can there be another fire?

1272
00:46:54,311 --> 00:46:56,687
- There's nothing left to burn.
- It's just ashes.

1273
00:46:56,688 --> 00:46:58,815
I hope no one's waiting in the car.

1274
00:46:58,816 --> 00:47:00,024
Please…

1275
00:47:00,025 --> 00:47:01,818
I'm so scared!

1276
00:47:01,819 --> 00:47:03,027
Let's go!

1277
00:47:03,028 --> 00:47:04,362
I want to go home.

1278
00:47:04,363 --> 00:47:05,488
You need to drive, Gabee.

1279
00:47:05,489 --> 00:47:07,074
SOBBING

1280
00:47:07,658 --> 00:47:09,785
FUMBLING

1281
00:47:10,410 --> 00:47:12,370
Do-hoon's quick to strap himself in.

1282
00:47:12,371 --> 00:47:13,996
RUSHING

1283
00:47:13,997 --> 00:47:15,290
- I'll reverse out of here.
- Okay.

1284
00:47:15,999 --> 00:47:17,458
Let's get going.

1285
00:47:17,459 --> 00:47:18,918
Gabee, are you okay to drive?

1286
00:47:18,919 --> 00:47:20,546
I'll give it a go, Yong-jin.

1287
00:47:22,631 --> 00:47:23,549
Oh, Gabee.

1288
00:47:24,842 --> 00:47:25,800
Oh, Gabee.

1289
00:47:25,801 --> 00:47:27,261
- I'm sorry.
- Are you okay?

1290
00:47:27,761 --> 00:47:28,971
- I'm sorry.
- It's okay.

1291
00:47:29,596 --> 00:47:30,555
It's all good.

1292
00:47:30,556 --> 00:47:32,807
- You're doing great.
- You're a good driver.

1293
00:47:32,808 --> 00:47:35,768
So, we're now heading to…

1294
00:47:35,769 --> 00:47:37,144
- Yonghadang Shrine.
- Yonghadang?

1295
00:47:37,145 --> 00:47:38,938
- It's Yonghandang.
- Yonghandang.

1296
00:47:38,939 --> 00:47:42,567
Is that the place
that Deok-u mentioned to King MS?

1297
00:47:42,568 --> 00:47:43,860
Wasn't that the garden?

1298
00:47:43,861 --> 00:47:45,319
- Was that Baeksudam Garden?
- Yes.

1299
00:47:45,320 --> 00:47:46,737
- It was the garden.
- That means

1300
00:47:46,738 --> 00:47:50,283
the abandoned house was Baeksudam Garden.

1301
00:47:50,284 --> 00:47:52,410
- That's right.
- The ritual is performed

1302
00:47:52,411 --> 00:47:54,662
- at Yonghandang Shrine.
- Yes.

1303
00:47:54,663 --> 00:47:56,873
We have to move around a lot today.

1304
00:47:56,874 --> 00:47:59,834
If we look at the map,
we need to head north.

1305
00:47:59,835 --> 00:48:01,627
Just follow the road straight up.

1306
00:48:01,628 --> 00:48:02,587
CURRENT LOCATION

1307
00:48:02,588 --> 00:48:03,713
Oh, my gosh.

1308
00:48:03,714 --> 00:48:05,548
I'm seriously so scared.

1309
00:48:05,549 --> 00:48:06,592
This is exhausting.

1310
00:48:07,092 --> 00:48:10,344
I feel like something might jump out.

1311
00:48:10,345 --> 00:48:11,888
Just follow the road.

1312
00:48:11,889 --> 00:48:13,056
- It's the garden.
- There's a sign.

1313
00:48:13,932 --> 00:48:15,725
It says it's been shut down.

1314
00:48:15,726 --> 00:48:17,393
This must be the reservoir.

1315
00:48:17,394 --> 00:48:19,437
- Yes, it is.
- We're at the reservoir.

1316
00:48:19,438 --> 00:48:20,898
I hate this.

1317
00:48:22,941 --> 00:48:24,568
It's a real reservoir!

1318
00:48:25,360 --> 00:48:26,986
- I can't believe it.
- This is insane.

1319
00:48:26,987 --> 00:48:28,696
It's the cursed reservoir.

1320
00:48:28,697 --> 00:48:29,822
It's too scary.

1321
00:48:29,823 --> 00:48:31,115
It's seriously so scary.

1322
00:48:31,116 --> 00:48:32,409
Why is it so scary?

1323
00:48:34,286 --> 00:48:36,454
BEEPING

1324
00:48:36,455 --> 00:48:37,455
It's at 70 percent.

1325
00:48:37,456 --> 00:48:39,373
It's gone past 78 and is now at 80.

1326
00:48:39,374 --> 00:48:40,709
It's going up that quickly?

1327
00:48:41,209 --> 00:48:43,544
- It's because we're near the water.
- This must be the source.

1328
00:48:43,545 --> 00:48:44,921
That explains it.

1329
00:48:44,922 --> 00:48:45,964
That must be it.

1330
00:50:30,318 --> 00:50:35,323
Subtitle translated by: Hannah Og Nam
